---
title: Modal Dialog
description: A modal using `:target` to show/hide without JavaScript.
slug: modal-dialog
cssFile: modal-dialog.css
explanation: The <code>:target</code> pseudo-class matches an element whose <code>id</code> matches the URL fragment. Clicking the open link sets the URL hash, which makes <code>:target</code> match and shows the overlay. Clicking the close link clears the hash (<code>href="#"</code>), hiding the modal. The overlay is <code>display:none</code> by default and <code>display:flex</code> when <code>:target</code>.
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<a class="modal-open-btn" href="#demo-modal">Open Modal</a>

<div class="modal-overlay" id="demo-modal">
	<div class="modal-box">
		<h3>Pure CSS Modal</h3>
		<p>This modal is controlled entirely by the URL hash and :target — zero JavaScript needed.</p>
		<a class="modal-close" href="#">Close modal</a>
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<a href="#my-modal">Open Modal</a>

<div class="modal-overlay" id="my-modal">
  <div class="modal-box">
    <h3>Modal Title</h3>
    <p>Modal content here.</p>
    <a href="#">Close</a>
  </div>
</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.modal-overlay {
  display: none;
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  background: rgba(0,0,0,.5);
  z-index: 200;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

.modal-overlay:target {
  display: flex;
}

.modal-box {
  background: #fff;
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 2rem;
  max-width: 400px;
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
